amme.pdf |access-date=12 December 2019  |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book |last=Farmelo |first=Graham |author-link=Graham Farmelo |title=Churchill's Bomb: How the United States Overtook Britain in the First Nuclear Arms Race |publisher=Basic Books |year=2013 |isbn=978-0-465-02195-6 |oclc=858935268 |location=New York |ref=harv |url-access=registration |url=https://archive.org/details/churchillsbombho0000farm }}\n* {{cite journal | last=Goldberg |first=Alfred | jstor=2610825 | title=The Atomic Origins of the British Nuclear Deterrent | journal=International Affairs |date=July 1964 | volume=40 | issue=3 | pages=409\u2013429 | doi=10.2307/2610825 |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite journal | last=Gott |first=Richard | title=The Evolution of the Independent British Deterrent | journal=International Affairs |issn=0020-5850 |date=April 1963 | volume=39 | issue=2 | pages=238\u2013252 | doi=10.2307/2611300 | jstor=2611300 | ref = harv }}\n* {{cite book |last=Gowing |first=Margaret |authorlink=Margaret Gowing |title=Britain and Atomic Energy 1939\u20131945  |publisher=Macmillan |year=1964 |location=London |oclc=3195209 |ref=harv }}\n* {{cite book |last = Gowing |first = Margaret   | first2 = Lorna | last2 = Arnold | authorlink2=Lorna Arnold | year = 1974a | title=Independence and Deterrence: Britain and Atomic Energy, 1945\u20131952, Volume 1, Policy Making | publisher= Macmillan| location = London | isbn = 0-333-15781-8| oclc = 611555258 | ref=harv }}\n* {{cite book |last = Gowing |first = Margaret  | first2 = Lorna | last2 = Arnold  | year=1974b  |title=Independence and Deterrence: Britain and Atomic Energy, 1945\u20131952, Volume 2, Policy and Execution  |location= London |publisher=Palgrave Macmillan|isbn=0-333-16695-7|oclc= 946341039 |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book |last=Hewlett |first=Richard G. |authorlink=Richard G. Hewlett |last2=Anderson |first2=Oscar E. |url=https://www.governmentattic.org/5docs/TheNewWorld1939-1946.pdf |title=The New World, 1939\u20131946 |publisher=Pennsylvania State University Press |year=1962 |isbn=0-520-07186-7|location=University Park |oclc=637004643 |ref=harv |accessdate=26 March 2013 }}\n* {{cite book |last=Hewlett |first=Richard G.  |last2=Duncan |first2=Francis |title=Atomic Shield, 1947\u20131952 |series=A History of the United States Atomic Energy Commission |url=http://energy.gov/sites/prod/files/2013/04/f0/Hewlett%20and%20Duncan%20-%20Atomic%20Shield%20%28complete%29.pdf |accessdate=7 March 2015 |publisher=Pennsylvania State University Press |location=University Park, Pennsylvania |year=1969 |isbn=0-520-07187-5|oclc=3717478 |ref=harv }}\n* {{cite book |last=Jones |first=Matthew |author-link=Matthew Jones (historian) |series=The Official History of the UK Strategic Nuclear Deterrent |title=Volume I: From the V-Bomber Era to the Arrival of Polaris, 1945\u20131964 |location=Abingdon, Oxfordshire |publisher=Routledge |year=2017 |isbn=978-1-138-67493-6 |oclc=957683181|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book |last=Macmillan |first=Harold |author-link=Harold Macmillan |title=Riding the Storm: 1956\u20131959 |url=https://archive.org/details/ridingstorm195611956macm |url-access=registration |location=London |publisher=Macmillan |year=1971 |isbn=978-0-333-10310-4 |oclc=198741 |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite report |last=Mills |first=Claire |title=UK-US Mutual Defence Agreement |date=17 September 2014 |publisher=House of Commons Library |url=https://www.nuclearinfo.org/sites/default/files/House%20of%20Commons%20Standard%20Note%20US-UK%20Mutual%20Defence%20Agreement%20Sept%202014.pdf |access-date=12 September 2017 |ref=harv }}\n* {{cite book|last=Moore|first=Richard|title=Nuclear Illusion, Nuclear Reality: Britain, the United States, and Nuclear Weapons, 1958\u201364|publisher=Palgrave Macmillan|series=Nuclear Weapons and International Security since 1945|location=Basingstoke, Hampshire|year=2010|isbn=978-0-230-21775-1|oclc=705646392|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book |last=Paul |first=Septimus H. |year=2000 |title=Nuclear Rivals: Anglo-American Atomic Relations, 1941\u20131952 |location=Columbus, Ohio |publisher=Ohio State University Press |isbn= 978-0-8142-0852-6|oclc=43615254 |ref = harv }}\n* {{cite report |last=Ritchie |first=Nick  |title=The UK Naval Nuclear Propulsion Programme and Highly Enriched Uranium |date=February 2015 |publisher=Federation of American Scientists |location=Washington, DC |url=https://fas.org/wp-content/uploads/2015/03/2015-FAS-UK-NNPP-HEU-final2.pdf |access-date=12 September 2017 |ref = harv }}\n* {{cite book |last=Wade |first=Troy E. II |editor-last=Mackby |editor-first=Jenifer |editor-last2=Cornish |editor-first2=Paul |title=US-UK Nuclear Cooperation After 50 Years |contribution=Nuclear Testing: A US Perspective |pp=200\u2013211 |location=Washington, DC |publisher=Center for Strategic and International Studies Press |year=2008 |isbn=978-0-89206-530-1 |oclc=845346116 |ref=harv }}\n* {{cite book |last=Wynn |first=Humphrey |year=1997 |title=RAF Strategic Nuclear Deterrent Forces, Their Origins, Roles and Deployment, 1946\u20131969. A documentary history |publisher=The Stationery Office |location=London |isbn=0-11-772833-0|ref=harv}}\n* {{cite journal |last = Young  |first = Ken |author-link=Ken Young |title=A Most Special Relationship: The Origins of Anglo-American Nuclear Strike Planning |journal=Journal of Cold War Studies |date=Spring 2007 |volume=9 |issue=2 |pages=5\u201331 |doi=10.1162/jcws.2007.9.2.5 |ref=harv}}\n* {{cite book  |last = Young  |first = Ken  |title = The American Bomb in Britain: US Air Forces' Strategic Presence 1946\u201364 |date = 2016  |location = Manchester  |publisher = Manchester University Press |isbn = 978-0-7190-8675-5 |oclc=942707047 |ref=harv}}\n{{refend}}\n\n==External links==\n* [http://www.nti.org/media/pdfs/56_4.pdf Full text of the Agreement]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20160308142716/http://www.acronym.org.uk/dd/dd77/77mda.htm Negotiations for extension to treaty] (2004)\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20080118030158/http://www.awe.co.uk/main_site/about_awe/history/timeline/1958/ US-UK Agreement], [[Atomic Weapons Establishment]]\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20041217064919/http://www.basicint.org/nuclear/MDAlegal.htm Mutual Defence Agreement and the Nuclear Non-Proliferation Treaty \u2013 Legal Opinion]\n\n{{Use British English|date=September 2017}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2012}}\n{{Portal bar|Politics|United Kingdom|Nuclear technology}}\n\n{{featured article}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:1958 US-UK Mutual Defence Agreement}}\n[[Category:1958 in military history]]\n[[Category:1958 in the United Kingdom|Mutual Defence Agreement]]\n[[Category:1958 in the United States|Mutual Defence Agreement]]\n[[Category:Cold War treaties]]\n[[Category:Nuclear history of the United Kingdom]]\n[[Category:Nuclear weapons program of the United States]]\n[[Category:Treaties concluded in 1958]]\n[[Category:United Kingdom\u2013United States treaties]]\n[[Category:United Kingdom\u2013United States military relations]]\n", "name_user": "118.71.135.178", "label": "unsafe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/1958_US%E2%80%93UK_Mutual_Defence_Agreement"}
{"title_page": "Supalonely", "text_new": "{{short description|2019 single by Benee}}\n{{Infobox song\n|name=Supalonely\n|type=single\n|artist=[[Benee]] featuring [[Gus Dapperton]]\n|EP=[[Stella & Steve]]\n|published=15 November 2019\n|released=6 December 2019\n|format={{hlist|[[Music download|Digital download]]|[[Streaming media|streaming]]}}\n|genre={{hlist|[[Disco]]<ref name=\"Idolator\" />|[[alt pop]]<ref name=\"Idolator\" />}}\n|length=3:43\n|label=[[Republic Records]]\n|writer={{hlist|[[Brendan Patrick Rice]]|[[Jenna Andrews]]|[[Josh Fountain]]|[[Stella Rose Bennett]]}}\n|producer={{hlist|Josh Fountain|Brendan Patrick Rice}}\n|chronology=[[Benee]]\n|prev_title=[[Monsta (song)|Monsta]]\n|prev_year=2019\n|year=2019\n|misc={{external music video|type=single|{{YouTube|Rb6Scz-5YOs|Supalonely}}}}\n}}\n\n\"'''Supalonely'''\" is a song by New Zealand musician [[Benee]]. It was initially released as a song on her second extended play ''[[Stella & Steve]]'' on 15 November 2019, before becoming the EP's third and final single on 6 December 2019.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://pilerats.com/written/light-easy/must-listen-singles-benee-spacey-jane-young-franco-more/|title=This Week's Must-Listen Singles: BENEE, Spacey Jane, Young Franco + more|last=Davies|first=Hayden|date=11 December 2019|website=PILERATS|url-status=live|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref> The song gained popularity after spawning a viral dance challenge on the online video-sharing platform [[TikTok]] in March 2020.<ref name=\"Idolator\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.idolator.com/7907879/future-hit-benees-supalonely-is-absolutely-irresistible|title=Future Hit: BENEE's \"Supalonely\" Is Absolutely Irresistible|last=Wass|first=Mike|date=10 March 2020|website=[[Idolator (website)|Idolator]]|url-status=live|access-date=13 March 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.clashmusic.com/videos/benees-supalonely-is-ultra-infectious|title=BENEE's 'Supalonely' Is Ultra-Infectious|last=Murray|first=Robin|date=6 March 2020|website=[[Clash (magazine)|Clash]]|access-date=13 March 2020}}</ref> The song peaked on charts of countries such as United Kingdom, Netherlands, Norway, Sweden and Ireland. The song entered the Top 40 of both the US and Global [[Spotify Velocity|Spotify Charts]], where on 10 March alone it gained 662,000 streams in the US and 1.84 million streams globally.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://headlineplanet.com/home/2020/03/11/benee-gus-dappertons-supalonely-reaches-new-peak-on-spotify-chart-enters-top-100-on-us-itunes-sales-chart/|title=BENEE & Gus Dapperton's \"Supalonely\" Reaches New Peak On Spotify Chart, Enters Top 100 On US iTunes Sales Chart|last=Cantor|first=Brian|date=11 March 2020|website=Headline Planet|access-date=13 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Critical reception ==\nOn his [[Apple Music]] show, [[Elton John]] described \"Supalonely\" as a \"smash record\", and further described Benee as \"an amazing young artist\" who \"writes really brilliantly\".<ref>{{Cite news|last=Barton|first=Monika|url=https://www.newshub.co.nz/home/entertainment/2020/03/elton-john-raves-about-amazing-benee-confesses-he-s-crazy-about-six60-on-apple-music-show.html|title=Elton John raves about 'amazing' Benee, confesses he's 'crazy about' Six60 on Apple Music show|date=6 March 2020|work=Newshub|access-date=15 March 2020|url-status=live|language=en}}</ref> Ariana Marsh from [[I-D|''i-D'']] wrote that the \"sunny pop\" song \"turns your typical breakup song on its head\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://i-d.vice.com/en_uk/article/jgeg8b/benee-and-gus-dapperton-turn-breakup-blues-into-sunny-pop-on-supalonely|title=BENEE and Gus Dapperton turn breakup blues into sunny pop on Supalonely|last=Marsh|first=Ariana|date=4 February 2020|website=[[i-D]]|language=en|url-status=live|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref> The song was described by Glenn Rowley of ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' as \"a quirky, knowing ode to the art of loneliness.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/pop/8550207/benee-supalonely-video-tour-dates|title=Benee Is 'Supalonely' in Colorful New Video, Announces North American Tour: See the Dates|last=Rowley|first=Glenn|date=5 February 2020|website=Billboard|url-status=live|access-date=15 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Charts ==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2020)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Australia ([[ARIA Charts|ARIA]])<ref name=\"ARIA\">{{cite web|url=http://www.ariacharts.com.au/charts/singles-chart|title=ARIA Australian Top 50 Singles|publisher=[[Australian Recording Industry Association]]|date=30 March 2020|accessdate=28 March 2020}}</ref>\n| 9\n|-\n{{single chart|Austria|22|artist=Benee feat. Gus Dapperton|song=Supalonely|rowheader=true|accessdate=26 March 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Flanders|48|artist=Benee feat. Gus Dapperton|song=Supalonely|rowheader=true|accessdate=28 March 2020}}\n|-\n{{single chart|Wallonia Tip|8|artist=Benee feat. Gus Dapperton|song=Supalonely|rowheader=true|accessdate=28 March 2020}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Canada ([[Canadian Hot 100]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/charts/search?artistname=Benee&chartcode=CAN|title=Benee, CAN|work=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]|accessdate=31 March 2020}}</ref>\n| 23\n|-\n{{single chart|Czechdigital|25|year=2020|week=13|rowheader=true|accessdate=31 March 2020}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Denmark ([[Tracklisten]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://hitlisten.nu/default.asp?w=12&y=2020&list=t40|title=Track Top-40 Uge 12, 2020|publisher=[[Hitlisten]]|accessdate=1 April 2020}}</ref>\n| 22\n|-\n{{single chart|Finland|18|artist=Benee|song=Supalonely|rowheader=true|accessdate=30 March 2020}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| France ([[Syndicat National de l'\u00c9dition Phonographique|SNEP]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://snepmusique.com/les-tops/le-top-de-la-semaine/top-albums/?semaine=12?&annee=2020&categorie=Top%20Singles|title=Top Singles (Week 12, 2020)|publisher=[[Syndica